# TokenLean — Token Optimisation Framework — GCP Deployment Environment
# Copy to .env.gcp and fill in your values. .env.gcp is gitignored — NEVER commit it.
#
# Usage:
#   source .env.gcp && ./scripts/gcp/gcp-deploy.sh
#   source .env.gcp && ./scripts/gcp/start-gcp.sh
#   source .env.gcp && ./scripts/gcp/stop-gcp.sh

# ─── GCP Project ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GCP_PROJECT_ID=your-gcp-project-id
GCP_REGION=asia-south1

# ─── Config GCS Bucket (auto-created by Terraform if left blank) ──────────────
CONFIG_GCS_BUCKET=
CONFIG_GCS_BLOB=config/config.yaml

# ─── Terraform State (auto-created by gcp-deploy.sh if left blank) ────────────
TF_STATE_BUCKET=${GCP_PROJECT_ID}-tf-state

# ─── LLM Keys ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Under strict BYOK (the commercial default), NO platform provider key is seeded into
# the project (SKIP_PLATFORM_KEYS=true) — every tenant supplies its own. So config/keys.yaml
# is NOT required for a commercial GCP deploy.
#
# The one place an operator key is still needed on GCP is TESTING: the harness tenants
# (--ptp) and key-security-harness each need a real OpenAI key to seed as their own BYOK
# key (Fernet-encrypted per-tenant into tenant_provider_keys — it never becomes a platform
# key). deploy-commercial-gcp.sh sources this file with `set -a`, so LLM_KEY_OPENAI set here
# is exported and used by the --ptp seeding + the harness. Set it to run the GCP test suite:
# LLM_KEY_OPENAI=sk-...

# ─── Optional: SendGrid (portal verification / password-reset emails) ─────────
# Commercial deploy only (deploy-commercial-gcp.sh). Unset → the portal falls back
# to a FakeEmailSender that just logs the verification link (fine for dev/staging);
# real emails won't send until this is set and you re-deploy. Stored as a Secret
# Manager secret (sendgrid-api-key) on token-proxy.
# SENDGRID_API_KEY=

# ─── Optional: BYOK provider-key hardening (commercial deploy; default ON) ─────
# deploy-commercial-gcp.sh sets all three infra flags TRUE by default. Uncomment to
# opt OUT of any of them (e.g. a first-time apply that needs a reachable DB, or an
# unhardened dev stack). See scripts/commercial/commercial-deploy-readme.md §8A.
# HARDEN_KMS=false          # do NOT KMS-wrap the master key (plaintext Secret Manager)
# HARDEN_SECRET_IAM=false   # keep the project-wide secretAccessor grant (no per-secret IAM)
# HARDEN_PRIVATE_SQL=false  # keep public Cloud SQL IPv4 (needed if you add external psql/migration)

# ─── Optional: Routing (G06) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cascade complexity judge model — referenced by config.yaml groups.G6_routing.judge_model.
# Empty/unset = built-in word-count heuristic. Set (e.g. gpt-4o-mini) for LLM-scored confidence.
# G06_JUDGE_MODEL=

# ─── Optional: Proxy scaling ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cloud Run --max-instances ceiling for the token-proxy service (capacity/cost knob).
# Default 1. Tenancy is safe under multi-instance (identity resolved per-request from
# the API key — no in-process state). After raising, re-run the isolation suite /
# a concurrent two-tenant smoke to confirm no cross-tenant bleed.
# PROXY_MAX_INSTANCES=1
